$interpreted: Hanbei: Minnie! How could you do such a thing? Why would you burn Sophie's luggage?
Hutchinson: Hanbei, do you think Mrs. Minnie is the one who burnt the bags?
Minnie: Why would you accuse me of doing such a thing?
Minnie: Uhh...
Hutchinson: Miss Minnie, where does it hurt, exactly?
Hutchinson: Hanbei, didn't the doctor say to not destabilize her emotions? Leave it for now.
Rune: I caught...the bad man.
Hanbei: Hmph. If you want to know about Minnie's condition, why don't you ask the doctor yourself?
Hutchinson: Huh?
Doctor: Ouch! That hurts!
Hutchinson: Aren't you a doctor? Why would you burn Sophie's bags?
Doctor: I didn't want to, Minnie told me to do it.
Hutchinson: Miss Minnie, what is going on here?
Minnie: I was scared. Scared that my Soph would leave with you...
Hanbei: So you burned her clothes so she wouldn't be able to perform?
Hanbei: Actually, you never were sick in the first place. You were just pretending to be sick to keep Sophie by your side.
Hutchinson: Faked being sick!? So you're not really sick?
Minnie: I didn't think I'd be caught. It's true. I'm not sick.
Hanbei: How could you trick Sophie?
Minnie: If I didn't have to trick her I wouldn't. But if I didn't do that, there is no way she would leave you.
Minnie: You all know how difficult life in the circus is.
Minnie: If you want what's best for her, please don't make her take on such a large burden.
Hutchinson: Ever since Morgan passed away, Sophie has taken on the responsibility of running the circus. It has been so hard...
Sophie: Mom, are you okay...?
Sophie: Huh? Why is everybody here? What's the doctor doing here?
Minnie: Soph, come here. I've something to tell you.
Minnie: Soph, the doctor just said I need more rest. It's not good to have so many people living here...
Hutchinson: Miss Minnie! This...
Hanbei: The doctor's right. Minnie ought to rest in peace. Let's head back to the circus.
Hanbei: Sophie, you stay here and take care of your mom.
Hutchinson: Hanbei...!?
Ru-yi: Hanbei, are you serious? We're just going to leave Sophie here and run away?
Sophie: You're going to leave me here!?
Hanbei: Rune is able to perform for you. We don't need you anymore.
Sophie: What did you just say? That's a little much, don't you think!?
Hanbei: You're the ringmaster and yet our income hasn't increased at all over the years. Looks to me like you're not cut out to be a ringmaster.
Hanbei: Why don't you stay here and live the life of a lady? That'd be best for you...
Sophie: Best for me...?
Hutchinson: Hanbei...
Sophie: What's that, you dirty prick!? You'll see how badly you need me!
Sophie: Without me, how boring will that circus be!?
Hanbei: Hmph, I don't think so. Ru-yi, Hutchinson, Rune, let's go.
Rune: Sophie...
Sophie: Not being a ringmaster is a breeze! Mom, I'm hungry. Let's go get something to eat.
Minnie: Soph, do you really want to stay with me?
Sophie: Of course. After all, you're still sick~
Minnie: But...
Sophie: Mom, didn't you say it's rare that you feel this well? Let's go for a walk on the town. I'll take you out tomorrow~
